title: Lake Geneva, Wisconsin Study for new Fire and Police Station

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Study for a future Fire/Police Station on SE corner of Townline Road and Highway 120, parcel ZSB 00331

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Gary Milliette

title: Vehicle registration records for license plate 43440U from 1970-1983

communications.subject: Pennsylvania Right to Know Act Request: Vehicle registration records for license plate 43440U from 1970-1983
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Pennsylvania Right to Know Act, I hereby request the following records:

Vehicle registration records from July 1, 1970 (or whatever date the Pennsylvania Department of Transportation started registering vehicles with state license plates, if later than July 1, 1970) until January 1, 1983, for tag number: 43440U

I need the records of the vehicle with license plate 43440U in Pennsylvania because I need to establish to whom the vehicle was registered through the year 1982. Such records should include the vehicle description, the name(s) of the owner of the vehicle, the registration plate number, and any addresses associated with the owner(s) of the vehicle.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Making an Exoneree
